84
00:05:55,644 --> 00:05:56,944
That's right!

85
00:05:56,944 --> 00:05:58,337
Excuse me.

86
00:05:58,337 --> 00:06:01,644
Do you know Officer Wataru Takagi, children?

87
00:06:01,644 --> 00:06:03,544
What?

88
00:06:03,544 --> 00:06:05,644
Yes, we do. But why?

89
00:06:05,644 --> 00:06:07,644
I couldn't have asked for better.

90
00:06:07,644 --> 00:06:12,744
He asked me to hand this over to his detective girlfriend.

91
00:06:12,744 --> 00:06:16,044
Could you do so for me?

92
00:06:16,044 --> 00:06:20,344
Are you referring to Officer Sato whom we were just talking about?

93
00:06:20,344 --> 00:06:23,344
Do you mean you also know that female detective?

94
00:06:23,344 --> 00:06:24,363
Yes.

95
00:06:24,363 --> 00:06:27,144
She's strong and scary like an ogre though.

96
00:06:27,144 --> 00:06:28,367
Well, well...

97
00:06:28,367 --> 00:06:31,044
But she's very pretty, too!

98
00:06:31,044 --> 00:06:32,044
That's right!

99
00:06:32,044 --> 00:06:34,944
I'm sure they're getting married soon!

100
00:06:34,944 --> 00:06:37,844
-Right! -They're really in love, you see!

101
00:06:37,844 --> 00:06:42,844
Then, please relay this message from him to the happy female detective.

102
00:06:43,944 --> 00:06:47,344
He said that it's perishable, so open it as soon as you can.

103
00:06:47,344 --> 00:06:49,344
He also said that it will be no good

104
00:06:49,344 --> 00:06:53,144
by tomorrow or the day after tomorrow.

105
00:06:53,144 --> 00:06:55,044
Hey!

106
00:06:55,044 --> 00:06:57,444
Conan!

107
00:06:57,444 --> 00:07:00,399
Okay, I'm counting on you guys.

108
00:07:00,399 --> 00:07:02,044
Who is that guy?

109
00:07:02,044 --> 00:07:04,403
He seems to be an acquaintance of Officer Takagi.

110
00:07:04,644 --> 00:07:06,944
By the way, where are Doc and Ai?

111
00:07:06,944 --> 00:07:09,344
It seems that Doc has a cold after all.

112
00:07:09,344 --> 00:07:11,444
I asked him to go home with Ai.

113
00:07:11,444 --> 00:07:13,144
What?

114
00:07:13,144 --> 00:07:15,244
Well, Doc's acting sick

115
00:07:15,244 --> 00:07:19,444
because he can't allow Ai's picture to be put on the pamphlet.

116
00:07:19,444 --> 00:07:21,344
So, does that mean Ai's not going to appear on it?

117
00:07:21,344 --> 00:07:22,421
That's too bad.

118
00:07:22,421 --> 00:07:25,444
I'm disappointed, too.

119
00:07:25,444 --> 00:07:29,744
I thought that I'd get to see the much rumored Dr. Agasa.

120
00:07:29,744 --> 00:07:31,444
Mr. Amuro.

121
00:07:31,444 --> 00:07:33,644
I heard from Master Mouri

122
00:07:33,644 --> 00:07:35,944
that the members of the Youth Detective Squad

123
00:07:35,944 --> 00:07:38,044
would be coming over to the MPD on Dr. Agasa's car today

124
00:07:38,044 --> 00:07:41,644
to take pictures to be put on the pamphlet.

125
00:07:41,644 --> 00:07:45,144
I was told to come to the MPD, too.

126
00:07:45,144 --> 00:07:47,144
I've already finished what I had to do though.

127
00:07:47,144 --> 00:07:48,447
Why were you told to come here?

128
00:07:48,447 --> 00:07:51,744
It was about the case back when you were kidnapped,

129
00:07:51,744 --> 00:07:55,444
and I stopped the car that you were in by crashing into it.

130
00:07:55,444 --> 00:07:57,544
They were questioning me again,

131
00:07:57,544 --> 00:08:00,044
saying that I might have gone overboard.

132
00:08:00,044 --> 00:08:01,444
Come to think of it,

133
00:08:01,444 --> 00:08:05,244
Masumi also said that she was told to come to the MPD again.

134
00:08:05,244 --> 00:08:09,244
In her case, she absolutely went overboard.

135
00:08:09,244 --> 00:08:11,244
Well, I also came here

136
00:08:11,244 --> 00:08:13,544
because I had something else to do.

137
00:08:13,544 --> 00:08:15,044
Something else to do?

138
00:08:15,044 --> 00:08:17,544
Don't worry about it.

139
00:08:17,544 --> 00:08:20,479
Because I don't have to do it anymore.

140
00:08:20,644 --> 00:08:22,481
Conan.

141
00:08:22,481 --> 00:08:24,483
Who was the young man?

142
00:08:24,483 --> 00:08:27,844
He's the private detective who became Pop Kogoro's disciple.

143
00:08:27,844 --> 00:08:30,489
A detective?

144
00:08:30,489 --> 00:08:32,491
He's good-looking.

145
00:08:32,491 --> 00:08:35,144
By the way, isn't Officer Takagi here yet?

146
00:08:35,144 --> 00:08:37,544
It seems like he's forgotten.

147
00:08:37,544 --> 00:08:39,744
I can't get through to him either.

148
00:08:39,744 --> 00:08:43,044
Then, why don't we try calling Officer Chiba?

149
00:08:43,044 --> 00:08:44,503
If so...

150
00:08:44,503 --> 00:08:46,505
Let's call Officer Sato!

151
00:08:46,505 --> 00:08:49,144
Since this is perishable.

152
00:08:50,744 --> 00:08:52,511
What?

153
00:08:52,511 --> 00:08:54,844
Officer Takagi was in tears while looking at the mini photo

154
00:08:54,844 --> 00:08:56,515
he had attached on his memo pad?

155
00:08:56,744 --> 00:08:57,844
Yes, ma'am.

156
00:08:57,844 --> 00:09:00,944
It looked like a cute photo at first glance,

157
00:09:00,944 --> 00:09:04,044
so I asked him if that photo was of you, Officer Sato.

158
00:09:04,044 --> 00:09:05,544
Cut the joke!

159
00:09:05,544 --> 00:09:08,244
And he got really angry at me.

160
00:09:08,244 --> 00:09:09,944
"Cut the joke"?

161
00:09:09,944 --> 00:09:11,844
He told me not to say anything

162
00:09:11,844 --> 00:09:14,144
because he wanted to explain it himself.

163
00:09:15,644 --> 00:09:17,544
Hey! Where is Officer Takagi?

164
00:09:17,544 --> 00:09:20,844
I wonder, too. I haven't seen him yet today.

165
00:09:25,844 --> 00:09:28,944
Yes, hello.

166
00:09:28,944 --> 00:09:30,144
Conan?

167
00:09:31,344 --> 00:09:34,544
Officer Takagi has something for me?

168
00:09:34,544 --> 00:09:37,044
Did the unknown man say that to you?

169
00:09:37,044 --> 00:09:39,444
-Yeah. -Here it is!

170
00:09:39,444 --> 00:09:41,244
What is going on here?

171
00:09:41,244 --> 00:09:42,844
He hasn't even shown up at work yet.

172
00:09:42,844 --> 00:09:45,144
Officer Takagi isn't here yet?

173
00:09:45,144 --> 00:09:47,544
That man told us that it's perishable,

174
00:09:47,544 --> 00:09:49,544
so he told us to eat it by tomorrow or the day after tomorrow.

175
00:09:49,544 --> 00:09:53,244
But this tablet doesn't look edible.

176
00:09:53,244 --> 00:09:55,044
It's a tablet.

177
00:09:55,044 --> 00:09:58,044
It could be a video letter, then.

178
00:09:58,044 --> 00:10:00,844
I'm sure he was too embarrassed to tell you in person.

179
00:10:00,844 --> 00:10:04,044
Officer Takagi is shy, you see.

180
00:10:04,044 --> 00:10:06,585
Seriously. If you have something to tell me,

181
00:10:06,585 --> 00:10:08,587
why can't you say it directly to me?

182
00:10:10,944 --> 00:10:12,944
O... Officer Takagi!

183
00:10:12,944 --> 00:10:15,044
There's a rope tied around his neck!

184
00:10:15,044 --> 00:10:16,595
If so, he can't get away.

185
00:10:16,595 --> 00:10:20,599
But if he's just tied up and lying down...

186
00:10:20,599 --> 00:10:22,601
-It switched. -Yes.

187
00:10:22,601 --> 00:10:24,603
It's taken from a different camera angle.

188
00:10:24,603 --> 00:10:25,944
Wait... Wait a second!

189
00:10:25,944 --> 00:10:27,844
If he turns over and falls...

190
00:10:27,844 --> 00:10:30,244
He'll be strangled and get killed!

191
00:10:30,244 --> 00:10:31,644
Get up, Officer Takagi!

192
00:10:31,644 --> 00:10:33,844
Get up and get a hold of your circumstances!

193
00:10:38,617 --> 00:10:40,044
Officer Takagi.

194
00:10:42,644 --> 00:10:44,623
Where...

195
00:10:47,444 --> 00:10:49,744
Where is this place?

196
00:10:54,633 --> 00:10:57,296
Calm down. Calm down.

197
00:10:57,296 --> 00:10:59,496
Think. Try to recall

198
00:10:59,496 --> 00:11:01,396
how things turned out this way.

199
00:11:01,396 --> 00:11:04,296
If I remember correctly, I met with that person last night,

200
00:11:04,296 --> 00:11:06,296
and was told that he wanted to show me some scenery,

201
00:11:06,296 --> 00:11:08,647
so he brought me here.

202
00:11:08,647 --> 00:11:11,996
Then, I was suddenly drugged from behind.

203
00:11:11,996 --> 00:11:14,653
But why?

204
00:11:14,653 --> 00:11:17,396
Don't tell me that he wanted to...

205
00:11:17,396 --> 00:11:19,896
Which means that the image on this camera

206
00:11:19,896 --> 00:11:22,096
is being sent to the MPD.

207
00:11:22,096 --> 00:11:23,496
What?

208
00:11:23,496 --> 00:11:26,396
Officer Takagi was kidnapped by someone?

209
00:11:26,396 --> 00:11:29,696
Yes, sir! This is the image of him.

210
00:11:29,696 --> 00:11:32,096
Officer Takagi!

211
00:11:32,096 --> 00:11:34,196
The camera switched over?

212
00:11:34,196 --> 00:11:36,096
There are probably three cameras.

213
00:11:36,096 --> 00:11:40,096
The shots are taken from the front, the side, and below.

214
00:11:40,096 --> 00:11:42,196
They seem to be streamed randomly.

215
00:11:42,196 --> 00:11:44,683
Can you tell where the images are being sent from?

216
00:11:44,683 --> 00:11:48,296
Yes, if we let the cyber crime department handle this.

217
00:11:48,296 --> 00:11:51,596
I don't think anything can be done right away.

218
00:11:51,596 --> 00:11:52,996
Conan!

219
00:11:52,996 --> 00:11:55,796
The only thing that can be done with that tablet

220
00:11:55,796 --> 00:11:56,996
is to switch the image on and off

221
00:11:56,996 --> 00:11:59,896
by pressing the button on the front of it.

222
00:11:59,896 --> 00:12:01,496
It's made so that everything else including the touch panel,

223
00:12:01,496 --> 00:12:06,496
power switch and the connector to charge it cannot be used.

224
00:12:06,496 --> 00:12:08,296
But Conan.

225
00:12:08,296 --> 00:12:10,396
If we disassemble this tablet,

226
00:12:10,396 --> 00:12:12,996
it can be charged directly from the inside.

227
00:12:12,996 --> 00:12:15,696
The data can also be transferred from the hard disk.

228
00:12:15,696 --> 00:12:17,696
Wouldn't we at least be able to figure out

229
00:12:17,696 --> 00:12:19,196
where the information is being sent from?

230
00:12:19,196 --> 00:12:20,719
What if we aren't able

231
00:12:20,719 --> 00:12:24,723
to view Officer Takagi's footage after we disassembled it?

232
00:12:24,723 --> 00:12:26,996
The culprit has remodeled the button,

233
00:12:26,996 --> 00:12:30,196
and embedded a program to invalidate the functions

234
00:12:30,196 --> 00:12:31,696
of the touch panel and all, you know?

235
00:12:31,696 --> 00:12:33,896
So, it'd be safer to think that this device is rigged

236
00:12:33,896 --> 00:12:36,296
so that the image would be cut off,

237
00:12:36,296 --> 00:12:38,196
and will never boot again if it is disassembled.

238
00:12:38,196 --> 00:12:40,396
Well, we could contact the provider

239
00:12:40,396 --> 00:12:45,696
and trace the tablet without having to go through something so risky.

240
00:12:45,696 --> 00:12:47,196
But culprits that carry out something like this

241
00:12:47,196 --> 00:12:50,296
would most likely be using a server abroad,

242
00:12:50,296 --> 00:12:52,496
so I think it would be difficult to trace the origin of the transmission

243
00:12:52,496 --> 00:12:54,753
in a short time.

244
00:12:56,496 --> 00:12:59,196
That's what Shinichi told me when I discussed this over the phone

245
00:12:59,196 --> 00:13:00,759
with him a while ago.

246
00:13:00,759 --> 00:13:02,761
But if it's possible to trace it,

247
00:13:02,761 --> 00:13:05,396
even if we have to spend some time...

248
00:13:05,396 --> 00:13:08,767
But the time limit is tomorrow or the day after tomorrow, right?

249
00:13:08,767 --> 00:13:10,296
Tomorrow or the day after tomorrow?

250
00:13:10,296 --> 00:13:14,773
The man who gave the tablet to Genta and the others said so.

251
00:13:14,996 --> 00:13:17,796
He told them that it's perishable, so it should be opened quickly.

252
00:13:17,796 --> 00:13:21,196
Otherwise, it'll become no good tomorrow or the day after tomorrow.

253
00:13:21,196 --> 00:13:23,196
What... What on earth does that mean?

254
00:13:23,196 --> 00:13:27,696
It probably means that if he's left as is, tied up and all...

255
00:13:27,696 --> 00:13:30,396
Without water or food, he won't make it past the third day.

256
00:13:30,396 --> 00:13:33,896
In other words, we only have until the day after tomorrow.

257
00:13:34,996 --> 00:13:38,496
But why does Officer Takagi have to go through something like this?

258
00:13:38,496 --> 00:13:42,396
He's not the type that would be hated by people.

259
00:13:42,396 --> 00:13:45,196
